Dear AmigaETag user,

    This program was originally planned to be released as shareware at a
cost of $5 US.  Unregistered users were to be allowed a 30 day evaluation
(with built-in "annoyance" features) period to decide if they liked the
program.  If so, registration would entitle the user to a keyfile that would
"unlock" the program and make it fully usuable (using a revolutionary new
keyfile protection scheme I have been developing over the past year).

    Unfortunately, I will be moving to New York soon to take a new job.
With this sudden additional responsibility, I will have very little time to
continue development on AmigaETag.  Rather than let this very useful utility
simply wither away and die as a project "almost finished", I have decided to
remit the program and all source code (in E) to the public domain.

    In this archive you will find the complete AmigaETag package, complete
with ASCII and AmigaGuide documentation and full source code.  Feel free to
use them as you wish.  However, if you plan to do further development on the
program, I ask only that the name of the program remains "AmigaETag" and
that I am given credit (both in the documentation and executable,
preferably) as the contributor of the program.

    Many months (and long programming hours) of development have gone into
this product.  While much of it will never be seen by the general public (as
it related to the keyfile protection system), I hope that you find this
program as useful as I have.  It is my sincerest hope that development of
this product continues and allows AmigaETag to reach the widest audience
possible.

